Behind every great smile is a great toothbrush doing the work! I love my @oralb iO8 brush, I’ve had it for about three years now and it's been amazing for taking care of my teeth, ESPECIALLY now that I’m pregnant. Pregnancy causes A LOT of changes to happen to the entire body, including the teeth and gums. Gum swelling, new eating habits, and even morning sickness can cause plaque and bacteria buildup which can cause gingivitis!
I brush my teeth a lot more now to get the funky taste out of my mouth, so having a brush that I love just makes brushing more enjoyable. What I love about the iO brush is the technology and size (it's small enough to get to the back of my mouth). It has a smart pressure sensor that provides instant feedback, the light turns red if I’m not brushing too hard, which is great because I’m heavy handed! There’s 6+ brush modes, I can adjust the sensitivity level and it times my brushing to make sure my teeth are free of bacteria that could be potentially harmful to me and Baby. You can even use an app on your phone to track your brushing habits! #OnlyiO gives you that deep clean feeling like you just left the dentist and leaves you with healthier teeth and gums!
The iO was the #1 gift guide recommendation for toothbrushes in 2021, so it's the perfect gift for anyone during the holiday season! Check out the @oralb iO8 toothbrush, linked in my story! #OralBWow #OralBHoliday #ad

And to think, at one point I thought this was something I couldn’t do. I spent most of my life believing that I wasn’t woman enough. I remember in 2018 I made a YouTube video talking about how I was afraid of the person that I am now without even knowing what this would look like. I knew this version of me existed in the future but didn’t know when or how I would get here and was running from the responsibility and the work I’d have to put in to become this person. 

Now let’s be clear, I had a right to be worried, it took a lot of self reflection and letting things go to get to where I’m at now, I cried a lot of tears during the pandemic 😂 But now that I fully accept myself and that responsibility of who God created me to be, I’m very confident in who I’m becoming. I felt like this as SOON as I turned 30. A year and a whole baby in my belly later and I feel more like myself, especially in these last few weeks of pregnancy, than I have in my entire life. 

Needless to say, I’m grateful for this process and glad I accepted who God chose me to be me knowing that he made no mistake when he made me who I am. I’m ready to start this next journey of self discovery becoming a new woman, especially with my new bestie ✨ let’s go kiddo 💕

IT’S ALMOST TIME! I’m getting my body ready to push out this baby so for the next few weeks I’ll be going to @alignedmodernhealth to work on preparing my body for labor! I’ve been to Aligned for chiropractic care pre-baby, so the specialists at Aligned suggested I try acupuncture as a lot of their clients use it to help alleviate some of the symptoms we experience during pregnancy.

 Acupuncture has been scientifically proven to be effective in treating pain and discomfort by using small needles to promote blood circulation. This activates your body’s immune and nervous systems, reducing inflammation and releasing endorphins to alleviate pain. During this pregnancy I’ve experienced a lot of swelling in my wrists and ankles, so those were the main target areas that we needled for this appointment. Overall it was a very relaxing experience!

Next week I’ll be getting acupuncture again and also doing chiropractic care as well, so stay tuned to see other ways we’re prepping my body for labor! #AlignedModernHealth

We’re back at @alignedmodernhealth today doing some chiropractic work! Pregnancy has definitely taken a toll on my mobility and my back, so I was excited for this appointment to address some of the common concerns mamas have while carrying a whole infant, especially at the end of the third trimester!

After my acupuncture session I met with the chiropractor. He was very gentle and gave really good insight on how I can best prepare for labor by stretching as well as giving me a much needed adjustment using the Webster technique! This technique aligns the pelvis and includes stretching of the attachment points of the uterine ligaments on the abdominal wall to soften the tissue, which will alleviate round ligament pain and assist in labor.

The plan is to keep going back every week for adjustments until the baby decides to pop! Stay tuned to see what else we do to prep for the baby’s arrival! #AlignedModernHealth

Products shown: Mixx Next + Pipa Urbn travel system in the color caviar

#myNuna #nunafamily #nunamixxnext #nunapipaurbn

Now that we’ve been using our @nuna_usa Mixx Next + Pipa Urbn travel system for over 2 months, I wanted to give my thoughts and review! If you watch the vlogs you know we test drove a few brands so here’s some reasons why we went with Nuna!

1. They have some of the lightest car seats on the market. My child is almost 13 lbs now 🥲 so a lightweight car seat was a must! Other car seats we looked at were just TOO heavy for my little arms 😂

2. The #NunaPipaUrbn has a baseless feature that allows us to remove it easily and put it in any car, which is clutch for carpooling and ride-sharing! I’ve been able to easily move the seat from my car to a friend’s car in minutes.

3. The #NunaMixxNext stroller has a sleek design, it rides super smooth and comes with a fully reclining seat so it works for newborns and toddlers.

4. The quality on both is superb. We also have a Doona car seat/stroller and while it’s convenient for traveling, it’s not an everyday stroller. The quality just does not compare. There’s also plenty of storage at the bottom of the Nuna and the sun shades extend farther and have plenty venting. 

We always get tons of compliments on how good these products look, Cam wanted a combo that was safe and sexy 😂 so that’s what we got!

I’m sad but grateful for what my body was able to do. Also - a bit relieved because breastfeeding (whether you feed from breast or exclusively pump or both) is an emotional rollercoaster and it was tiring. 

I struggled with DMER (dysphoric milk ejection reflex) for a good majority of my bf journey, which caused me to have a lot of sad, angry or anxious feelings every time I ejected milk. A lot of times I was pumping and crying 😭 and then it would stop after I was done. However I didnt let it stop me and I was still able to produce 50-60 oz a day for about 5 months. I took my whole medical grade pump with me on trips and pumped around the clock. I filled my freezer until there was no more space. I even donated some to those who needed it.

While I could try to go longer, the next few months of my life I want to dedicate to focus on rehabilitation of my body, my mental health and getting back to myself. Pumping was a lot and kind of a hinderance for me, so I am excited to start to get my life back. Wherever you are in your bf journey, whether you overproduce or underproduce or decided not to at all, you are doing amazing. 💜

*the total oz calculations come from my baby tracker app.

Thankful for my lil family. God really gave me a son.

I’m 7 months postpartum and FINALLY starting to feel like myself again! ✨In the last few months my hormones have been shifting back to normal, I’ve been starting my period like clockwork, and I’ve been feeling more frisky 👀 so instead of living in fear of 2 under 2, I’ve been using the @naturalcycles app to learn more about my fertility! Let’s be clear, I do love my baby, but I am DEFINITELY not ready for baby #2 just yet 🙃 so this app has been HEAVEN SENT! 

Natural Cycles is a non-invasive, hormone free birth control app* that is powered by an algorithm that analyzes body temperature to calculate “green” or “red” days (green meaning not fertile and red meaning fertile) so you know whether or not you should abstain/use protection to prevent pregnancy each day. I’ve synced the NC° app with my @ouraring to record my daily temperature trend data and it’s a no brainer! I also take LH tests and add any symptoms or feelings I may have in the app, which has helped in calculating fertile days. The more data you add, the more green days you’ll have! I also LOVE that the app has Partner View, which allows my husband to see my daily fertility status. Not only does he know when he needs to use precaution, but he’s also more informed about my current mood and symptoms during the different cycle phases. Now I don’t have to explain to him why I started crying randomly in my luteal phase 😂

As a holistic girly, it’s been a goal of mine to learn how my body functions and take control of my fertility. While I’m currently using the app to prevent, I love that when I am ready to try for another I can use the same app to try to conceive as well. I highly recommend you try it if you’re looking for a natural birth control option! 

Use my code VICKY at Naturalcycles.com to get 20% off your annual subscription + free thermometer

*Natural Cycles is for 18+ and does not protect against STIs ✨AD
